cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language inference (NLI) systems and their performance on adversarial datasets. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks and pre-training, which are common topics in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. The paper also evaluates the robustness of models, which is a topic in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of syntax-related attacks, which could be relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category, as syntax is often used in image captioning and other visual language tasks.
